subSubSection.paragraph:
Pronotum (
Fig. 1
) weakly transverse, usually 1.05-1.10 times as broad as long and much broader than head (approximately 1.4 times as broad as head in relatively large specimens). Punctation rather dense and fine, but more distinct than that of head; interstices with more or less pronounced microreticulation (
Fig. 4
).

Elytra (
Fig. 1
) 0.8-0.9 times as long as pronotum; posterior portion of suture mostly more or less distinctly elevated in both sexes (
Fig. 5
); punctation distinct, somewhat asperate, and dense; interstices with shallow microreticulation visible only at high magnification (100 x). Hind wings fully developed. Metatarsomere I longer than the combined length of II-IV.

